OL,3,CAir fryers - Do you know the dangers?
OL,5,F"It may sound tedious, but taking just
OL,6,Ffive minutes to read the
OL,7,Fmanufacturer's instructions could
OL,8,Favert an accident, as not all air
OL,9,Ffryers are the same.
OL,11,F"Make sure the appliance is placed on
OL,12,Fa clean, stable surface away from
OL,13,Fwalls, cupboards and anything
OL,14,Fflammable. Your air fryer will
OL,15,Fcommonly have a vent, so it's
OL,16,Fimportant that this is not blocked or
OL,17,Fpositioned too close to a wall or plug
OL,18,Fsocket, which could melt if too close
OL,19,Fby.
